ed SCA. Prior pass's Docker DNS to the vuln-DB mirror was unreachable. |","+| Checkov | n/a | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |"," "," ## Complete findings inventory"," "," | # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |"," |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|","-| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |","-| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |","+| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop (prior critical) | critical | no | `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py:49` | fixed (remediated by debugging; verified cleared) |","+| 2 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:87` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 3 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:89` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 4 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:90` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 5 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:91` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 6 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:104` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 7 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:107` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 8 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:110` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 9 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py:113` | reported-only (false positive) |","+| 10 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |"," ","-`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual","-checks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.","+`total_findings = 10` = rows above. `critical_count = 0` (row 1 cleared; rows 2–10 are","+false positives / waived-below-floor). `warning_count = 0`. `fixed_count = 0` (the RLS","+remediation was authored by the debugging agent, not by this security pass; verified only)."," ","-## Critical finding detail (row 1)","+## Triaged false positives (rows 2–9): why they are not counted and need no committed ignore"," ","-**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**","+All 8 are `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` on `text(f\"…\")` calls in the new regression test's","+role-provisioning fixture: `CREATE ROLE …`, `GRANT …`, `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup OWNER","+TO …`, `REVOKE …`, `DROP ROLE …`. Verified non-exploitable:"," ","-The plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy","-`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL","-app.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:","+- **No user-controlled interpolation.** The only interpolated values are `role_name`","+  (`f\"ur_rls_owner_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\"` — internally generated hex), `role_password`","+  (module-local literal `\"test-owner-password\"`), and `original_owner` (read from the","+  `pg_tables` system catalog). None is reachable from any request input.","+- **Unparameterizable by construction.** These are PostgreSQL **DDL** statements; role and","+  table identifiers cannot be bound as query parameters — interpolation is the only option.","+- **Test-only** ephemeral fixture, never in the served application."," ","-- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE","-  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**","-  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.","-- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves","-  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),","-  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.","-- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So","-  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.","-- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE","-  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass","-  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,","-  not a deliberate exception.","+**No committed `.semgrepignore` / inline `# nosemgrep` is required here, and adding one would","+be gratuitous** — CI's merge gate runs `semgrep scan --config auto --severity ERROR --error .`","+(full tree), and `--config auto` provably does **not** surface this rule: the sibling","+`tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` is **committed at HEAD** (part of green","+`main`), carries the **byte-identical unsuppressed** 8-hit DDL pattern (0 `nosemgrep`), and","+the required `pipeline-ci` check is green — which is impossible if `auto` gated on","+`avoid-sqlalchemy-text`. The 8 hits here are surfaced only by the broader explicit","+`p/python`/`p/owasp-top-ten` packs this agent runs, not by CI's `auto` config. (The codebase","+does inline-`nosemgrep` this rule where a *source* path warrants it, e.g. `usage_repo.py:134`;","+the new test is left consistent with its unsuppressed committed sibling rather than forked.)"," ","-**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control","-is present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)","-uses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from","-`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /","-`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads","-are blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth","-backstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.","-","-**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward","-migration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:","-- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`","-- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`","-- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.","-","-This is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of","-`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`","-via `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`","-(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE","-each still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query","-result changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that","-completes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a","-fails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns","-zero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)","-rather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency","-bumps are routed (U-19/D2).","-","-**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the","-`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE","-migration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's","-awareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.","-"," ## Fixes applied"," ","-None. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a","-schema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so","-`fixed_count = 0`.","+None by this pass. The RLS critical was remediated by the debugging agent (migration `0004`","++ regression test); this pass verified the clearance. No code was modified during this","+re-scan."," ","-## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required","+## Could not remediate"," ","-- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +","-  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.","+None."," "," ## Action required"," ","-- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),","-  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date","-  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)","-  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.","+- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g`** (pytest 8.3.4 → safe `>= 8.4.0`): dev-only, CVSS 6.8","+  (below the 7.0 deploy-gate floor), already filtered in the committed `osv-scanner.toml`.","+  No action needed for this feature; bump opportunistically."," ","-## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)","+## STRIDE delta addendum"," ","-8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.","+Empty. The change set introduces **no new attack surface**: migration `0004` is a","+grant-semantics toggle on an existing table; the three test changes add no entry point,","+trust boundary, data flow, or privilege surface. `stride_new_threats = 0`."," ","-| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |","-|---|---|---|---|","-| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |","-| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |","-| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |","-| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |","-| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |","-| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |","-| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |","-| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |","-| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |","+## ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation"," ","-Efficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not","-IP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);","-async runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —","-error scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).","+Triggered chapters `V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16` — unchanged from the prior pass;","+the migration/test diff alters no application ASVS posture (it strengthens the V8","+authorization backstop by making the RLS policy effective for the owner role). L1+L2","+universal verified, no in-scope L3 selected, `l1_l2_missing = []`, `l3_in_scope_missing = []`,","+`reconciled = true`."," ","-## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)","+## Deterministic conjuncts (all true)"," ","-`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`","-route, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.","-Every one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against","-`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,","-stored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS","-inefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)","-","-## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)","-","-Ran the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).","-One hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a","-**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248","-only), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE","-clause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`","-with no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds","-no count.","-","-## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)","-","-Triggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.","-L1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).","-","-- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.","-- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.","-- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.","-- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the","-  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is","-  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.","-- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.","-- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the","-  6d finding.","-- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;","-  fail-closed central error envelope — met.","-","-`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS","-object-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop","-is captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).","-","-## Input / data surface reconciliation","-","-- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a","-  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a","-  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,","-  reconciled.","-- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.","-  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not","-  t